#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.239"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.239:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.239:0.2"
msgid "19. Āsīvisavagga"
msgstr "19. The Simile of the Vipers"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 239. Rathopamasutta → rathūpamasuttaṃ (bj) | rato (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.239:0.3"
msgid "239. Rathopamasutta"
msgstr "239. The Simile of the Chariot"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.239:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Tīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sukhasomanassabahulo viharati, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṃ khayāya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when a mendicant has three qualities they’re full of joy and "
"happiness in the present life, and they have laid the groundwork for ending "
"the defilements."

msgctxt "sn35.239:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi tīhi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "sn35.239:1.3"
msgid "Indriyesu guttadvāro hoti, bhojane mattaññū, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto."
msgstr ""
"They guard the sense doors, eat in moderation, and are committed to "
"wakefulness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.176"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.239:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant guard the sense doors?"

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti, "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī;"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in "
"the features and details."

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.3"
msgid ""
"yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ. Tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its "
"restraint."

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …"
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose …"

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …"
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue …"

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …"
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body …"

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī;"
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details."

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.9"
msgid ""
"yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its "
"restraint."

#. VAR: odhastapatodo → odhatapatodo (s1-3, km) | odhasatapatodo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.239:2.10"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, subhūmiyaṃ cātumahāpathe ājaññaratho yutto assa ṭhito "
"odhastapatodo. Tamenaṃ dakkho yoggācariyo assadammasārathi abhiruhitvā "
"vāmena hatthena rasmiyo gahetvā, dakkhiṇena hatthena patodaṃ gahetvā, "
"yenicchakaṃ yadicchakaṃ sāreyyapi paccāsāreyyapi."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a chariot stood harnessed to thoroughbreds at a level crossroads, "
"with a goad ready. Then an expert horse trainer, a master charioteer, might "
"mount the chariot, taking the reins in his right hand and goad in the left. "
"He’d drive out and back wherever he wishes, whenever he wishes."

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.11"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu imesaṃ channaṃ indriyānaṃ ārakkhāya "
"sikkhati, saṃyamāya sikkhati, damāya sikkhati, upasamāya sikkhati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant trains to protect, control, tame, and pacify "
"these six senses."

msgctxt "sn35.239:2.12"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant guards the sense doors."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.177"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.239:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhojane mattaññū hoti?"
msgstr "And how does a mendicant eat in moderation?"

msgctxt "sn35.239:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant reflects properly on the food that they eat."

msgctxt "sn35.239:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘neva davāya, na madāya, na maṇḍanāya, na vibhūsanāya, yāvadeva imassa "
"kāyassa ṭhitiyā, yāpanāya, vihiṃsūparatiyā, brahmacariyānuggahāya, iti "
"purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me "
"bhavissati, anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to continue and "
"sustain this body, avoid harm, and support spiritual practice. So that I "
"will put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and "
"so that I will keep on living blamelessly and at ease.’"

#. VAR: rohanatthāya → ropanatthāya (bj, pts1) | sevanatthāya (s1-3, km) | gopanatthāya (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.239:3.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso vaṇaṃ ālimpeyya yāvadeva rohanatthāya, "
"seyyathā vā pana akkhaṃ abbhañjeyya yāvadeva bhārassa nittharaṇatthāya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a person who puts ointment on a wound only so that it can heal; or "
"who oils an axle only so that it can carry a load."

msgctxt "sn35.239:3.5"
msgid "evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant reflects properly on the food that they eat."

msgctxt "sn35.239:3.6"
msgid ""
"‘neva davāya, na madāya, na maṇḍanāya, na vibhūsanāya, yāvadeva imassa "
"kāyassa ṭhitiyā, yāpanāya, vihiṃsūparatiyā, brahmacariyānuggahāya, iti "
"purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me "
"bhavissati, anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to continue and "
"sustain this body, avoid harm, and support spiritual practice. So that I "
"will put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and "
"so that I will keep on living blamelessly and at ease.’"

msgctxt "sn35.239:3.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhojane mattaññū hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant eats in moderation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.239:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant committed to wakefulness?"

msgctxt "sn35.239:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu divasaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi "
"cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant practices walking and sitting meditation by day, "
"purifying their mind from obstacles."

msgctxt "sn35.239:4.3"
msgid ""
"Rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ "
"parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"In the evening, they continue to practice walking and sitting meditation."

msgctxt "sn35.239:4.4"
msgid ""
"Rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappeti pāde pādaṃ "
"accādhāya sato sampajāno uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā."
msgstr ""
"In the middle of the night, they lie down in the lion’s posture—on the right "
"side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on "
"the time of getting up."

msgctxt "sn35.239:4.5"
msgid ""
"Rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ paccuṭṭhāya caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi "
"cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"In the last part of the night, they get up and continue to practice walking "
"and sitting meditation, purifying their mind from obstacles."

msgctxt "sn35.239:4.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti."
msgstr "This is how a mendicant is committed to wakefulness."

msgctxt "sn35.239:4.7"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sukhasomanassabahulo viharati, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṃ khayāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has these three qualities they’re full of joy and happiness "
"in the present life, and they have laid the groundwork for ending the "
"defilements.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.239:4.8"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
